Varkala Stay Guide – Save this for your next beach escape🌊
From budget hostels to luxe villas, here’s your go-to list of stays that actually live up to the hype.
Share this with your travel bestie and start planning!

Hostels & Community Stays (₹1k–₹1.5k/night)
For solo travelers and social butterflies:
• Cliff & Coral
• Zostel Varkala
• Molly’s Hostel
• Hope Hostels
• The Hostel Stories
• The Gpsy Walker

Budget Hotels & Airbnbs (₹3k–₹6k/night)
Comfortable picks for couples & groups:
• Pura Vida
• Inda Hotel
• Glass Villa
• The Meadows Varkala
• Cliff & Coral (private options too!)

Luxury Escapes (₹7k onwards)
Where every morning starts with ocean views:
• Cliff Stories
• Elixir Cliff Beach Resort
• Villa Jacaranda
• Gateway Varkala
• Trip is Life

All of these are rated 4.2+ on Google and 8.8+ on Booking.com, so you’re set for a good time.

Note:
While most properties boast killer locations, not all have the best rooms. This list filters the best of both worlds—view and vibe.

Where I stayed:
Trip is Life & Cliff Stories – both offer dreamy ocean views and gorgeous rooms. Highly recommend if you’re in for the full Varkala experience.

Coorg’s 3 day itinerary 🌳

🚍 How to Reach:

From Bangalore or Coimbatore, go for a scenic ride or book a KSRTC bus online to Coorg. Upon arrival, rent a scooty (approx. ₹600/day) for convenient local travel.

🗓️ Day 1 – Explore Kushalnagar:
	•	Nisargadhama – A scenic river island with bamboo groves
	•	Dubare Elephant Camp – Interact closely with elephants
	•	Golden Temple (Namdroling Monastery) – A stunning Tibetan monastery

🛌 Stay Options in Kushalnagar:
	•	Budget: TVR Resort – Offers luxury villas with bathtubs and pools
	•	Mid-range: Purple Palms Resort & Spa – Comfortable stay with good amenities
	•	Luxury: Amanvana Spa Resort – A tranquil resort by the river ￼ ￼

🗓️ Day 2 – Discover Madikeri:
	•	Abbey Falls – Coorg’s iconic waterfall
	•	Mandalpatti Peak – Sunrise and jeep ride adventure
	•	Glass Bridge – Thrilling valley views
	•	Coffee Plantations – Aromatic evening strolls

🛌 Stay Options in Madikeri:
	•	Budget: Treebo Yajna Comforts
	•	Mid-range: Woodstock Villas – Cozy villas with great views
	•	Luxury: Taj Madikeri Resort & Spa – A luxurious retreat amidst nature ￼ ￼

🗓️ Day 3 – Explore Somwarpet:
	•	Abbey Matte Falls – A hidden gem amidst nature
	•	Mallalli Falls – Majestic and offbeat
	•	Pushpagiri Hills – A scenic trekker’s paradise

🛌 Stay Options in Somwarpet:
	•	Budget: Paloor Heritage Homestay
	•	Mid-range: Ayatana Coorg – A resort with beautiful views and amenities
	•	Luxury: Evolve Back, Coorg – A luxurious stay amidst coffee plantations ￼ ￼ ￼

☕ Where to Eat:
	•	Cafés: Big Cup Café, Alpha Café
	•	Restaurants: Rain Tree, Fort Mercara, The Bellies, Udupi, Shanti Sagar

Save this itinerary for your perfect Coorg escape!

From cozy boho corners to candlelit cliffside dinners, it’s a vibe you’ll want to stay in forever. The kind of place where time slows down, and your heart feels full🤍

It’s one of those places that stays with you ,long after you’ve left. The kind you’ll keep daydreaming about on random Tuesdays.
